definition: (particle) 1. introductory exclamation like English 'Oh' or 'Well; 2. mikiya 'to say "ah". 3. grammatical function marking attribution; 4. affix added to transitive- verbs to indicate ability to perform a certain action. "asulat" to be able to write, "akwa" to be able to get, "apangan" to be able to eat; 5. lig. used between a noun and a descriptive word ending with a consonant, alternating with "ng" as in "manayun a pibaslan", 'fine wear".
